#: {{syn|en|Thesaurus:midnight}}
#* {{RQ:Noyes Poems|poem=The Highwayman|stanza=IV|pages=50–51|pageref=50|passage=She twisted her hands behind her; but all the knots held good! / She writhed her hands till her fingers were wet with sweat or blood! / They stretched and strained in the darkness, and the hours crawled by like years, / Till, now, on the stroke of '''midnight''', / Cold, on the stroke of '''midnight''', / The tip of one finger touched it! The trigger at least was hers!}}
